<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2024-05-12T11:56:55.215+01:00" lasteditedby="44785" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">MT-POP-Cross-Over</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Crossover</keyword><keyword translate="true">Crossover Jerk</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="width:500px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:180px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MT-MD-Pop-Cross-over.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Cross-over - as accelerations changes 'sign'.]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Crossover: </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">the point at which the acceleration changes its sign </text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Crossover Jerk</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the rate of change of acceleration (Jerk) at </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">crossover</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">. It is important because this the time at which </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-POP-Backlash" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">backlash</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> traverses (nominally, in systems with no or very low friction). A </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">low jerk</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> means the acceleration does not change rapidly. When the acceleration does not change rapidly and the absolute acceleration is also near to zero, then the velocity does not change rapidly, also. Thus, impact after backlash also tends to be lower. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
